						               													<description>Horseshoes and Hand Grenades is a card flipping game of skill, strategy and luck. Players flip or drop cards onto a bandanna battlefield, attempting to score more points by grouping their soldiers together, getting soldiers into the double score bunker, and removing their opponent&amp;rsquo;s key scoring cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game includes high-quality plastic coated playing cards and a camouflage bandana that becomes the field of play. The game&amp;rsquo;s box innovatively opens into game components, the jeep and the bunker. Whimsical cartoon soldiers illustrated by Monte M. Moore make the game as attractive as it is enjoyable.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Group your soldiers into stacks containing sergeants and generals to increase your stack multiplier. Soldiers landing face down are injured, but can still be scored if you reach them with your medic. Cards that are flipped or dropped into the central bunker score double. Evacuate your high scoring stack before your opponent drops the bomb, get the highest score and win the game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
